Bobby Orr has more career points than Nick Lidstrom. Orr, who played for the Boston Bruins from 1966-1978, recorded 915 points in 657 regular season games and 92 points in 74 playoff games. Orr is widely regarded as one of the greatest defensemen of all time, known for his offensive prowess as well as his defensive skills. 

Nick Lidstrom, who played for the Detroit Red Wings from 1991-2012, recorded 1,142 points in 1,564 regular season games and 183 points in 263 playoff games. Lidstrom is also considered one of the greatest defensemen of all time and was known for his all-around game and leadership on the ice.